attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a malicious ELF binary, a downloader bot likely belonging to the Mirai/Satori family. The sample spreads by exploiting multiple command injection vulnerabilities in IoT devices. It contains functionality to exploit the Huawei Home Gateway vulnerability (CVE-2017-17215) via a SOAP request to `/ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1` and another vulnerability via a GET request to `/upgrade_handle.php`. Upon successful infection, it downloads and executes additional payloads (e.g., `.Sarm7`, `.Smips`) from the C2 server 89[.]213[.]193[.]98. The malware also enumerates processes via `/proc` to kill competing malware or security tools, using `/var/Angela` as a self-identifier.
